sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant C as Client
    participant GW as API Gateway
    participant P as Payments Service
    participant R as Redis (rate limit)
    participant DDB as DynamoDB (balance + ledger — money truth)
    participant PG as PostgreSQL (metadata + balance cache)
    participant MQ as Event Bus (Kafka)
    participant U as User Directory
    participant F as Fraud Engine
    participant X as ML / AML APIs (external)
    participant N as Notification

    rect rgb(225, 240, 255)
    Note over C,MQ: SYNCHRONOUS — debit only, then return 200 and fire event
    C->>GW: POST /v1/transfers (Idempotency-Key, JWT)
    GW->>GW: JWT verify / rate limit
    GW->>P: createTransfer(req)
    P->>PG: write transfers meta (status=DEBITED, note, idempotency_key)
    alt key exists (duplicate)
        PG-->>P: conflict → return stored response
        P-->>C: 200 (same as before)
    else new request
        P->>R: daily/per-txn limit check ($500 / $2,500)
        P->>U: resolve(email/phone) → recipientId
        P->>DDB: read sender's latest ledger entry → balance_after, seq
        Note over P,DDB: ONE DynamoDB TransactWriteItems (atomic, money truth)
        P->>DDB: put sender entry (seq+1, balance_after-=amt) cond: seq+1 not exists
        P->>DDB: put escrow entry (balance_after+=amt) cond: idempotency_key not seen
        DDB-->>P: committed (or ConditionalCheckFailed → balance/replay → retry/dedupe)
        P-->>C: 200 OK (transfer_id, status=DEBITED)
        P->>MQ: TransferRequested
    end
    end

    rect rgb(255, 248, 225)
    Note over DDB,PG: DynamoDB Streams → refresh PostgreSQL balance cache (async, display only)
    DDB-->>PG: stream balance change → update balance_cache_minor
    end

    rect rgb(235, 255, 235)
    Note over MQ,N: ASYNCHRONOUS WORKFLOW (state machine — Step Functions if it grows complex)
    MQ-->>P: (1) fraud step
    P->>F: fraud / AML check (suspicious merchant, etc.)
    F->>X: AML screening (+ ML scoring)
    X-->>F: result
    alt denied / manual review needed
        F-->>P: REVIEW or DENY
        Note over P,DDB: rare: human approval flow → on DENY, compensate
        P->>DDB: TransactWriteItems reverse: ESCROW → sender (phase=REVERSAL)
        P->>PG: transfers.status = CANCELLED
    else passed
        F-->>P: ALLOW
        Note over P: (2) moratorium — wait settle_after so the transfer can be cancelled
        P->>P: wait until settle_after (cancellable window)
        Note over P,DDB: (3) settlement — actual transfer (DynamoDB TransactWriteItems)
        P->>DDB: put escrow + recipient entries (phase=ESCROW_TO_RECIPIENT)<br/>each carries new balance_after, cond on latest seq + idempotency
        P->>PG: transfers.status = SETTLED
        P->>MQ: TransferSettled
    end
    MQ-->>N: (4) notify sender & recipient (Push/SMS/Email)
    end
